author: Daniel Henninger
title: It’s Trump’s Iran Deal Now
text:
It has been written or said maybe a million times that President Obama’s “signature” foreign-policy achievement was the Iran nuclear deal. Now they are calling President Trump’s withdrawal from the deal foreign-policy “vandalism.” Someone’s ox is getting gored.
In his first year, President Trump overturned most of Mr. Obama’s signature regulatory initiatives—also denounced as vandalism—and now the liberated U.S. and world economies are booming. Prudence, a dying virtue, suggests a wait-and-see attitude toward Mr. Trump’s...
